ther through the judicial review of transitional justice bills or the criminal trials of victimizers, institutions realize the value of respect and concern for all while contributing to a culture that is hospitable to democracy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aPolitical crimes and offensesxLaw and legislation. 0aPolitical crimes and offenses. 0aTransitional justice. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311063857808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2016z9783110485301oZDB-23-DPH40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/miha1765040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231541183423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231541183.jpg  a978-3-11-063857-8  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2016  aZDB-23-DPHb2016